Filter & Sorts
Filtering¬†docs
You can also include a filter in your payload. These differ from property type to property type, and may take some trial and error. Sorting can also be added to return everything in
payload = {
    "page_size": page_size,
    "filter": {
        "or": [
            {"property": "Status", "status": {"does_not_equal": "Done"}},
            {"property": "Tags", "multi_select": {"contains": "Improvement"}},
        ]
    },
    "sorts": [{"property": "Due", "direction": "ascending"}],
}

Properties
These can be a bit finicky to get working. These are the types that I‚Äôve got working so far. They go inside the properties: {} dictionary in the payload.








Type
Code
Note




checkbox
 "p_name": {"checkbox": true}
accepts a bool (True/False)


date
"p_name": {
    "date": {
        "start": datetime(2023, 5, 29).isoformat(),
        "end": None,
    }
}
requires from datetime import datetime, timezone


multi-select
"p_name": {"multi_select": [{"name": val}]}
accepts a list of named vals to select. If val doesn‚Äôt exist it will be created.


number
"p_name": {"number": num}



relation
"p_name": {"relation": [{"id": page_id, "name": page_name}]}
requires relation database to have integration and get the related page‚Äôs id


rich_text
"p_name": {"rich_text": [{"text": {"content": text}}]}



select
"p_name": {"select": {"name": val}}
like multiselect, if val doesn‚Äôt exist it will be created


status
"p_name": {"status": {"name": val}}
like multiselect but value must exist



